Docker & Kubernetes SRE Engineering Handbook (Production Guide)

This section is a production-focused guide for Senior Site Reliability Engineers (SREs) covering Docker, orchestration, Kubernetes, networking, deployments, debugging, and real-world incident response.

It is designed to take you from fundamentals → production architecture → cloud-native systems (AWS EKS).

1. Modern Containerized Architecture (SRE View)

Modern distributed systems follow this pipeline:

Application Code
↓
Docker Image
↓
Container Registry (Docker Hub / ECR / Private Registry)
↓
Kubernetes Cluster
↓
Deployments / Pods / Services
↓
Ingress Controller / Load Balancer
↓
Users / Traffic
SRE Responsibilities

A Senior SRE ensures:

System reliability under failure
Scalability under load
Observability (logs, metrics, traces)
Safe deployments & rollbacks
Infrastructure automation
